    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Police and Citizens</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Bruce Kerievsky says New York City Police Dept will be responsive to citizens' needs and values only when there is civilian supervisory board (June 29 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mayor's Panel Faults Police Department on Discipline System for Officers'' (news article, June 29): Isn't it clear that we will have a police force responsive to citizens' needs and values only when both the commissioner and the department report to a civilian supervisory board?</p>
        <p>BRUCE KERIEVSKY  Great Neck, N.Y., June 30, 2000</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Mayor's Panel Faults Police Department on Discipline System for Officers'' (news article, June 29): Isn't it clear that we will have a police force responsive to citizens' needs and values only when both the commissioner and the department report to a civilian supervisory board?</p>
        <p>BRUCE KERIEVSKY  Great Neck, N.Y., June 30, 2000</p>
      </block>
